{
  "stem": "12904.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Everything was there for the eventual pick up, or whatever, deportation or whatever they wanted to do--the extermination.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister was married and was living in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her husband had started on [NON-ENGLISH]-- that means he had started training for Israel in-- in agriculture.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And somehow the Germans, of course, they didn't really have to have an excuse, interpreted that as being a communist.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they withheld the passports of my sister and her husband at the time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We left in April, '37.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We could still pay for the fare on the And-- by the way, everything else we had to leave at the house, and money, and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We came with a few hundred dollars, I think.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or a few hundred marks.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But that's why we brought a lot of books-- the books that we could bring, but not much else.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we left.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were, of course, very upset that my sister and her husband could not leave at the same time, and were, you know, naturally trying to-- we gave affidavits.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we gave affidavits to my mother-- because we didn't have any money, really, we had to ask other people that we had met in St.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Louis to help us with affidavits for my mother's youngest brother, who was in concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Although he was married to a non-Jewish woman, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she got him out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's his wife, his Christian wife got him out of camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he had to leave within 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He went to England first, and then came to New York later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they came out a year and a half later, just before the famous Crystal Night, the Kristallnacht, with a little suitcase and a few dollars or a few marks.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
